<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-244-033 </DOCNO><DOCID>09 760 465</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  Jan 14 1991 v25 n2 p67(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Unisys adds to sales force with resellers. (Unisys Corp.)(includesrelated article on former NCR executive Hugh Lynch's appointmentto senior vice president of Unisys Computer Systems Product Group)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bozman, Jean S.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Unisys Corp is expanding its value-added reseller (VAR) programand plans to add new sales personnel in specific areas where itsproducts have sold well.andP;  The company, which is still strugglingto recover from a loss of $356.8 million in 3rd qtr 1990 and amassive layoff of 5,000 employees, will move in directly on largeaccounts and allow VARs to sell into smaller sites to reducedirect-sales overhead.andP;  Unisys plans to continue writing its ownoff-the-shelf applications, according to Computer Systems ProductsGroup Pres Cyril J. Yansouni.andP;  It has also adopted the IntegratedInformation Environment multivendor open-systems architecture forits products.andP;  Many large Unisys customers were already in theprocess of implementing mixed-vendor environments when the companybegan pushing its new solutions.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Unisys Corp. (Planning).andO;Ticker:    UIS.andO;Topic:     Strategic PlanningComputer industryMarketing StrategyValue-added resellers.andO;Feature:   illustrationportrait.andO;Caption:   Cyril J. Yansouni. (portrait)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>